783
00:46:53.478 --> 00:46:54.679
Yeah.

784
00:46:55.847 --> 00:46:57.615
The power went out for 8 minutes

785
00:46:57.748 --> 00:46:59.284
and 19.48 seconds.

786
00:46:59.417 --> 00:47:01.395
What that means exactly. we don't know at this time.

787
00:47:01.419 --> 00:47:03.488
Charlie. they talked back.

788
00:47:04.189 --> 00:47:05.290
What do you mean?

789
00:47:05.423 --> 00:47:07.325
The power goes out. and exactly 8 minutes.

790
00:47:07.458 --> 00:47:10.128
19.48 seconds later. it comes back on.

791
00:47:10.962 --> 00:47:12.563
What do you think that means?

792
00:47:14.632 --> 00:47:15.466
Whoa.

793
00:47:15.600 --> 00:47:16.902
So what?

794
00:47:17.035 --> 00:47:18.745
That's the exact amount of time that it takes sunlight

795
00:47:18.769 --> 00:47:20.005
to get to Earth.

796
00:47:20.138 --> 00:47:22.249
They waited and they responded in a universal constant.

797
00:47:22.273 --> 00:47:23.474
We showed them we understand.

798
00:47:23.608 --> 00:47:24.809
Yep. The-the speed of light.

799
00:47:24.943 --> 00:47:26.420
They-they would know the sun is everything to us.

800
00:47:26.444 --> 00:47:28.546
No energy. no power. no biological life.

801
00:47:28.679 --> 00:47:29.680
But what did they say?

802
00:47:29.814 --> 00:47:30.882
No idea.

803
00:47:31.016 --> 00:47:32.326
Bare minimum. they said that we hear you

804
00:47:32.350 --> 00:47:33.751
and we know where you are.

805
00:47:33.885 --> 00:47:35.820
It's still too soon to predict

806
00:47:35.954 --> 00:47:38.156
