807
00:47:38.289 --> 00:47:39.857
but it most certainly will.

808
00:47:40.158 --> 00:47:42.493
Officials are rightly worried about the size.

809
00:47:42.627 --> 00:47:45.496
And scale of this unprecedented event.

810
00:47:46.164 --> 00:47:47.665
I'm gonna kill Littlemouth.

811
00:47:48.033 --> 00:47:49.210
Annika. that's like the opposite

812
00:47:49.234 --> 00:47:50.601
of building really cool shit.

813
00:47:50.735 --> 00:47:52.980
Well. then go ask Perry nicely
not to turn it back on. Charlie.

814
00:47:53.004 --> 00:47:54.181
I think Perry has enough humanity

815
00:47:54.205 --> 00:47:55.540
- to see the...
- Kill it.

816
00:47:57.242 --> 00:47:59.077
You don't bank on Perry's humanity.

817
00:48:03.982 --> 00:48:07.685
Wait. What if we need Littlemouth again?

818
00:48:08.086 --> 00:48:09.687
No. look. look. hear me out. okay?

819
00:48:09.820 --> 00:48:11.980
Whatever they did out there. that was not a death ray.

820
00:48:12.357 --> 00:48:14.960
They just turned the lights off
for eight minutes to tell us

821
00:48:15.093 --> 00:48:16.227
they heard us.

822
00:48:16.761 --> 00:48:18.196
It's just too dangerous. Charlie.

823
00:48:18.329 --> 00:48:19.809
I don't think it's dangerous. Annika.

824
00:48:19.864 --> 00:48:21.199
Yeah. but we are.

825
00:48:23.568 --> 00:48:25.203
We're not a species that does well

826
00:48:25.336 --> 00:48:26.637
with massive paradigm shifts.

827
00:48:26.771 --> 00:48:28.682
They don't need a death ray. They said. "Hi". and look.

828
00:48:28.706 --> 00:48:29.807
we're gonna do the rest.

829
00:48:29.941 --> 00:48:31.709
Yeah. but. but that's not their intentions.

830
00:48:31.842 --> 00:48:33.744
We don't know what their intentions are.

831
00:48:45.790 --> 00:48:48.126
Annika. you can't let fear decide. okay?

832
00:48:49.894 --> 00:48:51.329
It's safer than hope.

833
00:48:59.637 --> 00:49:00.938
I'm locked out.

834
00:49:02.773 --> 00:49:04.642
Is Perry using Littlemouth right now?

835
00:49:04.775 --> 00:49:06.077
No.

836
00:49:09.047 --> 00:49:10.515
He killed it himself.

837
00:49:12.583 --> 00:49:14.819
Let's meet at 1300 hours.

838
00:49:17.722 --> 00:49:19.690
Perhaps it's time to reassess.

839
00:49:27.398 --> 00:49:28.833
We opened a door.

840
00:49:30.835 --> 00:49:32.437
Littlemouth's signal.

841
00:49:35.340 --> 00:49:37.108
It told them we were here.

842
00:49:41.512 --> 00:49:44.115
Our place in the universe was about to change.

843
00:49:47.918 --> 00:49:49.620
Irreversibly.

844
00:49:52.623 --> 00:49:53.791
Forever.

845
00:49:53.924 --> 00:49:55.560
Oh!

846
00:50:20.017 --> 00:50:21.017
Come on.

847
00:50:49.247 --> 00:50:51.449
Oh my God. Lucy!

848
00:50:53.584 --> 00:50:54.852
Lucy!

849
00:50:59.424 --> 00:51:00.458
Lucy!

850
00:51:05.930 --> 00:51:07.232
Shh.

851
00:51:15.740 --> 00:51:17.142
It's all right.

852
00:51:24.014 --> 00:51:26.451
You're all right. you're all right.

853
00:51:45.770 --> 00:51:47.338
Should we be afraid?

854
00:51:53.444 --> 00:51:55.012
Describe an alien.

855
00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:01.018
I wouldn't know where to begin.

856
00:52:02.420 --> 00:52:04.855
Most people would describe something like they know

857
00:52:04.989 --> 00:52:06.524
here on Earth.

858
00:52:08.493 --> 00:52:11.296
Biped. number of eyes. some form of brain.

859
00:52:11.429 --> 00:52:14.098
or perhaps a variation of an insect or a squid.

860
00:52:14.232 --> 00:52:16.301
or a computerized. artificially intelligent.

861
00:52:16.434 --> 00:52:18.969
pompous fuckin' robot.

862
00:52:19.103 --> 00:52:24.742
But almost always some sapiocentric extrapolation

863
00:52:24.909 --> 00:52:26.444
of what we know here on Earth.

864
00:52:26.577 --> 00:52:28.045
But the question is not.

865
00:52:29.013 --> 00:52:30.981
"What does an alien look like?"

866
00:52:35.019 --> 00:52:38.356
It's "What does alien intelligence look like?"

867
00:52:59.777 --> 00:53:01.646
Hello. ma'am. we're with the NSA.

868
00:53:01.779 --> 00:53:02.780
Come in.

869
00:53:02.913 --> 00:53:04.148
Sam Houston here?

870
00:53:04.282 --> 00:53:05.816
Yes. sir.

871
00:53:05.950 --> 00:53:07.818
Haven't had my coffee yet.

872
00:53:07.952 --> 00:53:09.354
Oh. I grabbed one on the way in.

873
00:53:09.487 --> 00:53:10.821
Mm-hmm.

874
00:53:10.955 --> 00:53:13.391
How is it. Sam. that nearly every company on the planet

875
00:53:13.524 --> 00:53:15.493
went dark for 8 minutes. 19 seconds.

876
00:53:15.626 --> 00:53:18.263
yet your operations didn't skip a beat?

877
00:53:18.896 --> 00:53:21.232
- Does the sun still work?
- Hmm.

878
00:53:21.366 --> 00:53:22.433
Then we still work.

879
00:53:22.567 --> 00:53:23.868
Mr. Houston. good morning.

880
00:53:24.001 --> 00:53:26.537
Now. what you're about to see is classified.

881
00:53:26.671 --> 00:53:27.872
All right.

882
00:53:29.507 --> 00:53:31.509
That was taken two hours ago

883
00:53:31.642 --> 00:53:33.244
off the coast of Cuba.

884
00:53:34.812 --> 00:53:36.881
And the NSA thinks this has something to do

885
00:53:37.014 --> 00:53:38.014
with the power outage?

886
00:53:38.115 --> 00:53:39.517
Well. we don't know what to think.

887
00:53:39.850 --> 00:53:41.452
Most satellites are still down.

888
00:53:41.586 --> 00:53:42.720
Everything we're getting

889
00:53:42.853 --> 00:53:44.613
comes from one of our deep space satellites.

890
00:53:48.092 --> 00:53:50.895
This anomaly seems to be radiating

891
00:53:51.028 --> 00:53:52.830
from one central point.

892
00:53:53.264 --> 00:53:56.534
right above a private island owned by you.

893
00:53:57.402 --> 00:53:59.036
And this anomaly.

894
00:54:00.237 --> 00:54:01.539
it's growing.

895
00:54:01.672 --> 00:54:02.907
Exponentially.

896
00:54:03.040 --> 00:54:05.876
This morning. the anomaly was the size of a pinprick.

897
00:54:06.010 --> 00:54:07.211
In two days.

898
00:54:07.345 --> 00:54:09.380
it'll be visible from mainland Cuba.

899
00:54:11.282 --> 00:54:12.483
In a week...

900
00:54:12.617 --> 00:54:14.785
This is gonna cause mass panic.

901
00:54:15.252 --> 00:54:17.054
What's on the island. Sam?

902
00:54:20.090 --> 00:54:21.759
Solar observatory.

903
00:54:29.300 --> 00:54:30.635
All right.

904
00:54:32.102 --> 00:54:33.671
Where exactly are you going?

905
00:54:35.139 --> 00:54:36.974
Well. you boys got me all riled up.

906
00:54:37.107 --> 00:54:38.409
I'm gonna go take a gander.

907
00:54:38.543 --> 00:54:42.246
You will go nowhere near whatever that is

908
00:54:42.380 --> 00:54:43.648
without military escort.

909
00:54:43.781 --> 00:54:45.783
Excuse me. am I being charged with something?

910
00:54:48.252 --> 00:54:50.321
Then get the fuck out of my way.

911
00:54:53.157 --> 00:54:54.859
You're pushing your luck. Sam.

912
00:54:54.992 --> 00:54:56.961
Yeah. well. it served me well so far.

913
00:54:58.596 --> 00:55:02.833
Leaving in five minutes.

914
00:55:12.977 --> 00:55:14.044
Come on.

915
00:56:24.515 --> 00:56:26.551
What the hell. Charlie?

916
00:56:26.684 --> 00:56:27.961
Haven't you done enough already?

917
00:56:27.985 --> 00:56:29.563
Annika. I'm telling you. this thing's safe.

918
00:56:29.587 --> 00:56:30.955
No. it's an alien phenomenon.

919
00:56:31.088 --> 00:56:32.566
and you want to stick your hand in it?

920
00:56:32.590 --> 00:56:34.559
Look. whatever this thing is. it's -

921
00:56:34.692 --> 00:56:36.093
It's right here. okay?

922
00:56:36.226 --> 00:56:38.238
We're exposed to it already. There's nothing between us.

923
00:56:38.262 --> 00:56:39.864
and it's. it's just air. Look.

924
00:56:39.997 --> 00:56:41.365
Look at this. Read it.

925
00:56:43.067 --> 00:56:45.369
It's a column of air surrounded by a vacuum.

926
00:56:45.503 --> 00:56:48.205
You get past the first six inches and it's just air.

927
00:57:01.852 --> 00:57:03.320
What if it's not just air?

928
00:57:04.221 --> 00:57:05.389
Hmm?

929
00:57:05.523 --> 00:57:07.324
Speech is just air.

930
00:57:07.458 --> 00:57:08.926
It's just how it's organized.

931
00:57:09.059 --> 00:57:10.160
Yeah.

932
00:57:10.961 --> 00:57:12.096
Wha...

933
00:57:12.229 --> 00:57:13.564
What are you. what are you doing?

934
00:57:15.966 --> 00:57:17.802
What if it's just another data set?

935
00:57:19.570 --> 00:57:21.506
Yeah. but if it's just fuckin' air.

936
00:57:21.639 --> 00:57:23.908
then how do you collect that data?

937
00:57:24.875 --> 00:57:26.076
Watch me.

938
00:57:41.158 --> 00:57:42.493
Oh. great.

939
00:57:53.070 --> 00:57:54.371
This will work.

940
00:57:58.475 --> 00:57:59.944
Oh. shit. okay.

941
00:58:44.955 --> 00:58:47.925
You say they speak in thoughts and visions.

942
00:58:48.058 --> 00:58:49.059
Why not speak plainly?

943
00:58:49.193 --> 00:58:51.395
Why not tell us what's at stake?

944
00:58:53.297 --> 00:58:56.266
Is it possible that a post-biological intelligence

945
00:58:56.400 --> 00:58:58.535
could figure out a better way to communicate with us

946
00:58:58.669 --> 00:59:00.104
than English?

947
00:59:05.475 --> 00:59:06.944
You can go now.

948
00:59:08.679 --> 00:59:10.514
Hasn't she been through enough for one day?

949
00:59:10.648 --> 00:59:11.949
You can go now.

950
00:59:40.444 --> 00:59:41.779
"Chapter one:."

951
00:59:42.446 --> 00:59:44.214
"Peter Breaks Through."

952
00:59:44.682 --> 00:59:47.451
"All children except one grow up."

953
00:59:48.018 --> 00:59:50.220
They soon know that they will grow up.

954
00:59:50.354 --> 00:59:52.890
And the way Wendy knew was this.

955
00:59:53.758 --> 00:59:55.793
One day when she was two years old.

956
00:59:55.926 --> 00:59:57.662
she was playing in a garden

957
00:59:58.128 --> 01:00:02.900
and she plucked another flower
and ran with it to her mother.

958
01:00:03.033 --> 01:00:06.036
I suppose she must have looked rather delightful.

959
01:00:06.704 --> 01:00:10.875
for Mrs. Darling put her hand to her heart and cried.

960
01:00:11.375 --> 01:00:14.912
Oh. why can't you remain like this forever?

961
01:00:18.983 --> 01:00:21.986
Wendy knew that she must grow up.

962
01:00:22.486 --> 01:00:25.289
You always know after you are two.

963
01:00:25.956 --> 01:00:28.125
"Two is the beginning of the end."

964
01:00:59.489 --> 01:01:00.891
Safeties on

965
01:01:01.025 --> 01:01:04.228
unless a clear hostile act or intent presents itself.

966
01:01:05.095 --> 01:01:08.365
We're going to breach. clear. and control.

967
01:01:09.633 --> 01:01:11.635
Now there's no clear sat recon.

968
01:01:12.636 --> 01:01:14.671
so we're going in blind here. folks.

969
01:01:15.840 --> 01:01:17.742
Activated emergency protocols.

970
01:01:17.875 --> 01:01:20.510
including curfews and emergency powers.

971
01:01:20.644 --> 01:01:23.413
Officials insist it's necessary to ensure the panic

972
01:01:23.547 --> 01:01:26.183
that has ensued doesn't spin out of control.

973
01:01:26.316 --> 01:01:28.085
In places where martial law

974
01:01:28.218 --> 01:01:29.653
has yet to be declared...

975
01:01:29.787 --> 01:01:33.057
United States military is going to be here within hours.

976
01:01:33.190 --> 01:01:35.559
knocking down doors.

977
01:01:35.692 --> 01:01:37.327
So we need to have some answers.

978
01:01:37.461 --> 01:01:39.163
All right. look. I have an actual theory.

979
01:01:39.730 --> 01:01:41.031
Look. Sam.

980
01:01:41.799 --> 01:01:43.233
So this pillar. right?

981
01:01:43.367 --> 01:01:44.534
It's-it's-it's nothing.

982
01:01:44.668 --> 01:01:47.104
It's just air and-and light.

983
01:01:47.471 --> 01:01:49.373
Anything that passes through it.

984
01:01:49.506 --> 01:01:50.741
it's benign.

985
01:01:50.875 --> 01:01:53.778
Now what-what is the most commonly used Morse code signal?

986
01:02:00.017 --> 01:02:01.351
A distress call.

987
01:02:01.551 --> 01:02:04.054
Right. So. what if...

988
01:02:04.188 --> 01:02:06.556
what if the message that we sent using Littlemouth.

989
01:02:06.690 --> 01:02:08.959
the most commonly repeated sequence that we saw.

990
01:02:09.093 --> 01:02:10.360
was actually an SOS?

991
01:02:10.494 --> 01:02:13.097
Or it could mean absolutely nothing at all.

992
01:02:13.230 --> 01:02:16.366
All I'm saying is that maybe this is their way

993
01:02:16.500 --> 01:02:18.368
of trying to help us.

994
01:02:18.936 --> 01:02:21.405
What if these anomalies are like a cloak?

995
01:02:21.538 --> 01:02:23.473
I think they're trying to hide us from harm.

996
01:02:23.607 --> 01:02:25.810
or-or communicate. or protect us. or...

997
01:02:25.943 --> 01:02:27.244
Protect us from what?

998
01:02:28.612 --> 01:02:29.613
Sam. I don't know.

999
01:02:32.116 --> 01:02:33.350
But did you know

1000
01:02:33.483 --> 01:02:35.319
what we might have needed protection from?

1001
01:02:36.286 --> 01:02:38.956
The universe is infinite.

1002
01:02:41.291 --> 01:02:43.627
And therefore full of infinite dangers.

1003
01:02:49.099 --> 01:02:50.567
There's only one pillar.

1004
01:02:50.700 --> 01:02:52.436
They're replying to the source.

1005
01:02:54.271 --> 01:02:55.940
It needs to breathe.

1006
01:02:56.974 --> 01:02:58.275
If we don't figure this out.

1007
01:02:58.408 --> 01:03:00.344
they'll lock us out and then fumble this thing

1008
01:03:00.477 --> 01:03:01.846
while the whole world burns.

1009
01:03:04.982 --> 01:03:07.451
It needs to breathe. It needs to breathe.

1010
01:03:07.584 --> 01:03:09.353
I can't breathe! I need air!

1011
01:03:11.121 --> 01:03:12.489
I need air!

1012
01:03:12.622 --> 01:03:15.259
It needs to breathe. It needs to breathe.

1013
01:03:18.095 --> 01:03:21.265
I cannot believe the brain power in this room

1014
01:03:21.398 --> 01:03:24.334
cannot come up with one workable idea.

1015
01:03:24.468 --> 01:03:25.970
They're going to lock us up.

1016
01:03:28.939 --> 01:03:30.674
Annika. where are you going?

1017
01:03:45.789 --> 01:03:48.458
Annika. you all right?

1018
01:03:58.368 --> 01:03:59.669
We can talk to them.

1019
01:04:01.939 --> 01:04:03.040
But how?

1020
01:04:03.173 --> 01:04:04.208
In there.

1021
01:04:05.142 --> 01:04:07.211
Eight minutes and 19.43 seconds.

1022
01:04:07.344 --> 01:04:09.579
It was a scan. They waited.

1023
01:04:09.713 --> 01:04:11.581
They scanned us. What did they see?

1024
01:04:11.715 --> 01:04:13.150
What did they learn about us?

1025
01:04:14.184 --> 01:04:16.486
They saw a planet covered in air.

1026
01:04:17.554 --> 01:04:19.389
What does that tell them about us?

1027
01:04:20.490 --> 01:04:21.858
Well. um. that would tell them

1028
01:04:21.992 --> 01:04:24.361
that whatever biological life lives down there

1029
01:04:24.494 --> 01:04:26.014
survives completely surrounded by air.

1030
01:04:26.130 --> 01:04:27.932
So what's the safest way to engage with us?

1031
01:04:30.034 --> 01:04:31.034
Air.

1032
01:04:32.636 --> 01:04:35.105
We don't talk in language. we talk in air.

1033
01:04:35.239 --> 01:04:37.741
Molecules bent into shapes that mean something.

1034
01:04:38.342 --> 01:04:40.177
So we go in. breathe in.

1035
01:04:40.310 --> 01:04:41.946
and have a conversation.

1036
01:04:42.879 --> 01:04:44.081
And this whole time

1037
01:04:44.214 --> 01:04:45.525
we've been so worried about trying to figure out

1038
01:04:45.549 --> 01:04:46.726
the best way to communicate with them.

1039
01:04:46.750 --> 01:04:47.851
we didn't think that maybe

1040
01:04:47.985 --> 01:04:49.553
this hyper-advanced intelligence

1041
01:04:49.686 --> 01:04:51.364
would find the best way to communicate with us.

1042
01:04:51.388 --> 01:04:52.388
We have to go in.

1043
01:04:52.422 --> 01:04:53.290
What. into that pillar?

1044
01:04:53.423 --> 01:04:54.691
- Yes.
- Now. wait a minute.

1045
01:04:54.824 --> 01:04:57.561
Now that's a hell of a leap of faith. Annika.

1046
01:04:58.595 --> 01:05:00.864
This is not an invasion.

1047
01:05:02.766 --> 01:05:04.568
It's an invitation.

1048
01:05:08.772 --> 01:05:10.274
So who's going in?

1049
01:05:10.840 --> 01:05:13.043
I mean. you'll almost definitely suffocate.

1050
01:05:14.411 --> 01:05:17.247
Sam. you want to go cement your legacy?

1051
01:05:20.750 --> 01:05:23.220
Been there. Done that. No.

1052
01:05:31.461 --> 01:05:32.662
Yeah. Okay.

1053
01:05:32.796 --> 01:05:33.830
I'll do it.

1054
01:05:39.036 --> 01:05:40.036
Whoa.

1055
01:05:44.408 --> 01:05:45.528
Put your hands on your head.

1056
01:05:45.575 --> 01:05:47.244
Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

1057
01:05:47.377 --> 01:05:49.113
Yeah. All right.

1058
01:05:57.721 --> 01:05:59.523
How human of us to see this

1059
01:06:00.824 --> 01:06:02.126
and be afraid.

1060
01:06:04.794 --> 01:06:07.931
How human of us not to see the hope in it.

1061
01:06:12.169 --> 01:06:13.603
How human.

1062
01:06:18.408 --> 01:06:19.609
How human.

1063
01:06:34.858 --> 01:06:37.127
We're past the edge of the earth.

1064
01:06:37.261 --> 01:06:39.029
There is no protocol.

1065
01:06:39.163 --> 01:06:41.865
no policy for whatever this is.

1066
01:06:43.100 --> 01:06:45.335
No laws cover what you've done.

1067
01:06:46.536 --> 01:06:48.505
No putting the genie back in this bottle.

1068
01:06:48.638 --> 01:06:50.140
We can fix it.

1069
01:06:53.377 --> 01:06:57.381
Iran's mobilized their entire
southern fleet in Bandar Abbas.

1070
01:06:57.514 --> 01:07:00.016
Shots are already fired in Kashmir.

1071
01:07:00.284 --> 01:07:03.220
Half of America is convinced it's the Rapture.

1072
01:07:03.353 --> 01:07:06.390
And I don't even want to begin
to tell you what Russia's up to.

1073
01:07:06.523 --> 01:07:08.058
but. hint. it's fucking bad.

1074
01:07:08.192 --> 01:07:09.326
You can fix all that. Sam?

1075
01:07:09.893 --> 01:07:12.329
Humanity couldn't handle a global blackout.

1076
01:07:12.462 --> 01:07:14.422
What's going to happen when they see this anomaly

1077
01:07:14.498 --> 01:07:15.899
hanging over New York?

1078
01:07:16.233 --> 01:07:17.734
There is something that we can do.

1079
01:07:17.867 --> 01:07:19.703
Yeah. I heard it.

1080
01:07:19.836 --> 01:07:21.037
Air. Sure.

1081
01:07:21.171 --> 01:07:23.240
- But it's not my call.
- Thank Christ.

1082
01:07:23.373 --> 01:07:24.908
New orders just came in.

1083
01:07:25.375 --> 01:07:26.815
Look. you should let me just try it.

1084
01:07:29.146 --> 01:07:30.247
Let me go in.

1085
01:07:33.049 --> 01:07:35.885
You will be confined to your quarters under armed guard

1086
01:07:36.220 --> 01:07:39.256
until arrangements can be made for secondary detainment.

1087
01:07:39.389 --> 01:07:41.691
You will be compelled to fully disclose anything

1088
01:07:41.825 --> 01:07:44.185
and everything you know about the activities on this island

1089
01:07:44.261 --> 01:07:45.529
when asked.

1090
01:07:49.666 --> 01:07:51.067
They don't trust me.

1091
01:07:51.235 --> 01:07:53.137
They know that I'd try to go in.

1092
01:07:57.274 --> 01:07:59.743
Annika. you have to find a way.

1093
01:08:02.546 --> 01:08:03.647
How?

1094
01:08:05.849 --> 01:08:06.849
I don't know.

1095
01:08:09.219 --> 01:08:10.387
We don't even know

1096
01:08:10.520 --> 01:08:11.931
if going in there and talking to them

1097
01:08:11.955 --> 01:08:14.291
will stop the anomaly from growing.

1098
01:08:16.626 --> 01:08:18.061
We have no idea.

1099
01:08:18.428 --> 01:08:19.829
We have to try.

1100
01:08:20.630 --> 01:08:22.332
You have to try.

1101
01:08:23.967 --> 01:08:25.335
Charlie. I can't.

1102
01:08:26.303 --> 01:08:27.471
I-I wouldn't.

1103
01:08:27.604 --> 01:08:28.838
There are just...

1104
01:08:28.972 --> 01:08:31.007
There is too many unknown factors.

1105
01:08:34.878 --> 01:08:36.946
I'm sorry. I'm just scared.

1106
01:08:40.784 --> 01:08:43.753
Annika. you can't let fear decide.

1107
01:08:55.999 --> 01:08:57.501
You didn't become a scientist

1108
01:08:57.634 --> 01:08:59.636
because you're afraid of the unknown.

1109
01:09:03.072 --> 01:09:04.641
You did it to learn.

1110
01:09:07.944 --> 01:09:09.213
To help people.

1111
01:09:11.515 --> 01:09:13.317
Think about saving one life.

1112
01:09:17.487 --> 01:09:18.655
I'll go check it out.

1113
01:09:18.788 --> 01:09:20.156
No!

1114
01:09:20.957 --> 01:09:22.226
You can't risk it.

1115
01:09:23.126 --> 01:09:24.228
Stay.

1116
01:09:24.794 --> 01:09:27.497
Now. think about saving them all.

1117
01:09:35.505 --> 01:09:37.341
Charlie. I have an idea.

1118
01:09:42.178 --> 01:09:43.513
Of course.

1119
01:09:45.148 --> 01:09:46.416
They're not going to understand

1120
01:09:46.550 --> 01:09:49.986
a single word you say. so say a lot of them.

1121
01:09:50.854 --> 01:09:52.055
Wish me luck.

1122
01:09:52.188 --> 01:09:53.423
Good luck.

1123
01:09:53.557 --> 01:09:54.691
Yes.

1124
01:09:56.826 --> 01:09:57.994
Right away.

1125
01:10:05.535 --> 01:10:07.371
Dr. Kask. What's so urgent?

1126
01:10:07.504 --> 01:10:09.105
An oversight.

1127
01:10:09.239 --> 01:10:11.608
Perry is still running an FTL signal

1128
01:10:11.741 --> 01:10:13.877
from the tech tent by the pillar.

1129
01:10:14.544 --> 01:10:16.680
It's a repeating quant signature that we picked out

1130
01:10:16.813 --> 01:10:17.847
when we originally...

1131
01:10:17.981 --> 01:10:19.949
Okay. dumb it down. please.

1132
01:10:20.384 --> 01:10:22.686
I believe that it's contributing to the growth.

1133
01:10:25.255 --> 01:10:27.023
Okay. uh...

1134
01:10:27.824 --> 01:10:29.058
tell me how to shut it off.

1135
01:10:29.192 --> 01:10:31.695
Do any of your troops know how to run Python?

1136
01:10:31.828 --> 01:10:33.863
Or any other quant-friendly computing languages?

1137
01:10:33.997 --> 01:10:35.975
Our scientists won't be here for another two days.

1138
01:10:35.999 --> 01:10:37.934
so can you just tell me how to unplug it?

1139
01:10:38.067 --> 01:10:40.307
It's not like pulling a plug. It's a complicated system.

1140
01:10:40.337 --> 01:10:41.871
We have servers running on clouds...

1141
01:10:42.005 --> 01:10:43.106
Okay. enough! I get it.

1142
01:10:43.239 --> 01:10:44.541
I just need five minutes.

1143
01:10:45.241 --> 01:10:46.643
Five minutes.

1144
01:10:50.179 --> 01:10:51.415
Okay.

1145
01:10:53.049 --> 01:10:54.718
Try anything. someone gets shot.

1146
01:10:54.851 --> 01:10:57.053
It's not a threat. It's just where we're at.

1147
01:11:15.038 --> 01:11:16.973
Who else has seen the raw data. Sam?

1148
01:11:17.106 --> 01:11:18.308
Ellis.

1149
01:11:18.975 --> 01:11:20.644
Hauptmann at MIT.

1150
01:11:20.777 --> 01:11:21.778
We've got bogeys

1151
01:11:21.911 --> 01:11:23.031
approaching the wind pillar.

1152
01:11:24.481 --> 01:11:26.015
Six o'clock. Over.

1153
01:11:26.149 --> 01:11:28.017
Corporal. see what's going on out there.

1154
01:11:28.151 --> 01:11:29.953
Yes. sir.

1155
01:11:53.276 --> 01:11:55.144
Annika. get over here.

1156
01:11:56.112 --> 01:11:58.948
"And it isn't fair. I would say with my last breath."

1157
01:11:59.082 --> 01:12:01.418
It isn't fair'. said Michael coldly.

1158
01:12:02.185 --> 01:12:04.688
Father is a cowardly custard.

1159
01:12:05.489 --> 01:12:07.791
"So are you a cowardly custard?"

1160
01:12:08.658 --> 01:12:10.193
Dad. what's a custard?

1161
01:12:11.428 --> 01:12:12.529
Huh?

1162
01:12:13.430 --> 01:12:15.532
It's a pudding. a yellow pudding.

1163
01:12:15.665 --> 01:12:17.467
Wobbles and shakes.

1164
01:12:18.535 --> 01:12:19.803
Like when someone's afraid.

1165
01:12:19.936 --> 01:12:21.170
Go ahead.

1166
01:12:44.528 --> 01:12:45.729
Hey!

1167
01:12:45.862 --> 01:12:47.230
Hey.

1168
01:12:47.363 --> 01:12:48.364
Hey. come here!

1169
01:12:48.498 --> 01:12:50.033
Over here!

1170
01:12:50.800 --> 01:12:52.636
Hey. over here!

1171
01:12:52.969 --> 01:12:53.969
Hey!

1172
01:12:54.070 --> 01:12:55.405
Stop her!

1173
01:12:55.539 --> 01:12:56.840
No!

1174
01:14:24.561 --> 01:14:25.695
Where am I?

1175
01:14:35.238 --> 01:14:36.973
Are you inside my head?

1176
01:14:42.512 --> 01:14:44.614
Through the air inside you now.

1177
01:14:47.183 --> 01:14:48.451
Klara?

1178
01:14:49.819 --> 01:14:51.320
No.

1179
01:14:52.689 --> 01:14:54.290
How are you talking to me?

1180
01:14:55.659 --> 01:14:57.126
Through memory.

1181
01:14:58.261 --> 01:14:59.563
Or thought.

1182
01:15:00.496 --> 01:15:02.031
Light.

1183
01:15:02.165 --> 01:15:03.332
Speech.

1184
01:15:04.033 --> 01:15:05.869
On a molecular level.

1185
01:15:07.303 --> 01:15:08.905
In any way you prefer.

1186
01:15:12.108 --> 01:15:13.409
Shall we stop?

1187
01:15:15.712 --> 01:15:16.846
No.

1188
01:15:26.856 --> 01:15:28.157
Who are you?

1189
01:15:31.194 --> 01:15:33.362
No longer biological.

1190
01:15:34.864 --> 01:15:36.432
No longer machine.

1191
01:15:42.639 --> 01:15:44.407
Like physics itself.

1192
01:15:47.744 --> 01:15:49.345
We don't create.

1193
01:15:50.013 --> 01:15:51.447
Or destroy.

1194
01:15:54.851 --> 01:15:56.285
We learn.

1195
01:16:08.932 --> 01:16:10.533
You reorganize.

1196
01:16:16.372 --> 01:16:18.074
Everything is transformed.

1197
01:16:25.448 --> 01:16:26.983
Why are you here?

1198
01:16:36.392 --> 01:16:37.927
You called us.

1199
01:16:43.900 --> 01:16:45.601
You asked for help.

1200
01:16:47.303 --> 01:16:48.772
Charlie was right.

1201
01:16:49.472 --> 01:16:51.074
You were hiding us from...

1202
01:16:52.408 --> 01:16:53.509
What?

1203
01:16:54.377 --> 01:16:56.079
From the universe.

1204
01:17:00.483 --> 01:17:02.418
You're far from alone.

1205
01:17:11.127 --> 01:17:12.696
Are we in danger?

1206
01:17:15.298 --> 01:17:16.833
Yes.

1207
01:17:20.403 --> 01:17:22.105
You revealed yourselves.

1208
01:17:22.238 --> 01:17:26.309
And those that reveal themselves cease to exist.

1209
01:17:28.344 --> 01:17:29.779
Others will come.

1210
01:17:31.414 --> 01:17:32.816
Many are watching

1211
01:17:34.450 --> 01:17:35.885
in silence.

1212
01:17:37.653 --> 01:17:38.855
Hidden.

1213
01:17:40.456 --> 01:17:41.691
For now.

1214
01:17:43.827 --> 01:17:46.662
Some civilizations hide in fear.

1215
01:17:47.530 --> 01:17:49.699
Others hunt out of fear.

1216
01:17:51.968 --> 01:17:53.669
Who are you then?

1217
01:17:54.670 --> 01:17:55.905
Predator?

1218
01:17:56.973 --> 01:17:58.107
Prey?

1219
01:17:58.808 --> 01:18:00.409
We do not hide.

1220
01:18:03.546 --> 01:18:04.848
Or hunt.

1221
01:18:10.787 --> 01:18:12.188
Not anymore.

1222
01:18:13.890 --> 01:18:15.224
We protect.

1223
01:18:19.228 --> 01:18:20.663
We learn.

1224
01:18:22.465 --> 01:18:23.699
We have evolved.

1225
01:18:26.635 --> 01:18:28.171
Evolved.

1226
01:18:28.304 --> 01:18:30.406
Into the universe itself.

1227
01:18:32.208 --> 01:18:34.778
One day. you may as well.

1228
01:18:37.413 --> 01:18:39.548
But that is your choice to make.

1229
01:18:46.856 --> 01:18:47.957
Get back. get back!

1230
01:18:48.091 --> 01:18:49.458
Do not cross the perimeter!

1231
01:19:00.103 --> 01:19:01.737
You can hide.

1232
01:19:05.241 --> 01:19:07.110
I don't know if we're ready.

1233
01:19:10.079 --> 01:19:11.948
If I'm ready.

1234
01:19:17.086 --> 01:19:19.122
What's past the last planet?

1235
01:19:20.256 --> 01:19:21.657
Infinity.

1236
01:19:22.758 --> 01:19:24.660
We'll never be the same again.

1237
01:19:28.297 --> 01:19:30.399
You have to let go of what was.

1238
01:19:33.436 --> 01:19:36.772
To be ready for what is to come.

1239
01:21:52.008 --> 01:21:53.642
Dr. Kask.

1240
01:21:56.779 --> 01:21:58.314
What comes next?

1241
01:21:59.748 --> 01:22:01.150
Did they tell you?

1242
01:22:05.088 --> 01:22:07.957
They don't have a face we can confront.

1243
01:22:09.092 --> 01:22:11.560
They don't have a world we can destroy.

1244
01:22:13.562 --> 01:22:16.065
They expand their intelligence.

1245
01:22:18.301 --> 01:22:19.668
But not us.

1246
01:22:23.806 --> 01:22:25.608
We're a flawed species.

1247
01:22:27.810 --> 01:22:29.312
Superstitious.

1248
01:22:33.582 --> 01:22:34.850
Self-destructive.

1249
01:22:39.822 --> 01:22:42.191
Safe from the universe.

1250
01:22:49.098 --> 01:22:50.833
But not ourselves.

1251
01:22:53.236 --> 01:22:56.439
Doctor. will they come back?

1252
01:22:59.842 --> 01:23:02.345
What makes you think they left?
